19 (11) The department shall publish an annual game count, estimating to the department's best ability
20 the numbers of each species of game animal, as defined in 87-2-101, in the hunting districts and administrative
21 regions of the state. In preparing the publication, the department may incorporate field observations, hunter
22 reporting statistics, or any other suitable method of determining game numbers. The publication must include
23 an explanation of the basis used in determining the game count.
24 (12) The department shall report current sage grouse population numbers, including the number of
25 leks, to the Montana sage grouse oversight team, established in 2-15-243, and the environmental quality
26 council in accordance with 5-11-210 on an annual basis. The report must include seasonal and historic
27 population data available from the department or any other source.
